      "notes": "Non-string DEFC values are rejected despite matching valid codes numerically."
    }
  ],
  "mismatches": [
    "Docs limit AssistanceAwardTypeCodes to '02'-'11', but live validation also accepts '-1'.",
    "Docs describe DEFC as CARES Act codes, yet validation allows additional entries including numeric strings and 'QQQ'."
  ],
  "gaps": [
    "Meaning and intended usage of the '-1' award_type_codes value remains undocumented despite being accepted."
  ],
  "risks": [
    "Clients must handle both HTTP 400 and 422 validation errors with differing message formats.",
    "DEFC and award type enumerations appear centrally managed and may change without notice; avoid hard-coding beyond observed values.",
    "Unrecognized filters are silently ignored, which can hide misconfigured requests that callers expect to affect results."
  ]
}
